LongDescription: Cargo Feeders are small cargo ships designed to transport bulk materials from minor ports to major ones, where it can be loaded onto larger ships for long distance transport.  The large amount of internal space in these ships means they have plenty of room for large weapons.  Additionally, their small surface area means the refit shipyards were able to cover the hull in thick armor plates, something which would be impractical on the larger lineships.
FlavorText:
Constantine,

Baron Blackwood seized a fleet of container feeders bound for Bethel from the Locke Terminal in Roclaren, he's already transferred control over to the Otdel and Bulwark has been contracted to work on ships of a similar build. Personally, this is a great catch, these feeders could match the utility of the Alliance Raines and have enough room to mount most of our casemate weapons. They're still civilian ships, however, so don't expect them to suddenly go toe-to-toe with the Alliance's dedicated warships.

Vance has the most experience with these and thinks they're best used as a form of satellite ship guarding Ocellos or providing some extra firepower to the container ships. Personally, I think they'd be best used as an ambusher with our new Jinn weapons but I'm just a logistics officer, so you'll know better than I.

- Amelie, Logistics Command
